<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>Open the image in the Capture Editor</li>
            <li>Select <span class="Emphasis">Edit &gt;  Insert Image &gt; Cursor File</span>. </li>
            <li>In the dialog, locate and double-click the file. That image is added to the main image as an object.</li>
            <li>
                <p>To move the image object, hover over it until your cursor displays as an arrow <img src="../../../Images/Shared/Ca-Co-Fl-Mi/General/Arrow-Cursor.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. Then click and drag the object to a new location on the main image.</p>
                <div class="topic-only">
                    <div class="note">
                        <p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #fdc80b;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">If you have dragged the object outside the current boundaries of the image, padding is automatically added to compensate for the space needed. Double-click the image (not the image object) to open the File Properties dialog. Then, on the <span class="Emphasis">Appearance</span> tab, use the fields in the <span class="Emphasis">Background</span> section as necessary. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">For field descriptions, see <a href="../../../../Capture/Interface/Dialogs/File-Properties-Dialog.htm">File Properties dialog</a>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Shared/All/General/Save-File.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>